# Firebase Conventions

- TypeScript strict mode for Cloud Functions
- Validate all client input; never trust client-supplied roles
- Use server timestamps for official records
- Firestore rules: deny by default; institution-scoped access
- Players must not write official ranks, medals, or final results
- No secrets in source; use Secret Manager or CI secrets
- Audit log sensitive admin operations
